        " : \"لَيْسَ اَلْحُكْرَةُ إِلاَّ فِي اَلْحِنْطَةِ وَ اَلشَّعِيرِ وَ اَلتَّمْرِ وَ اَلزَّبِيبِ وَ اَلسَّمْنِ وَ اَلزَّيْتِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3954 - It is narrated from Ghiyath bin Ibrahim, who reported from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as):\n\"Hoarding (Ihtikar) applies only to wheat, barley, dates, raisins, ghee, and oil.\""
        ]
